column75: Heat/ice packs/infrared heating pad/infrared heat and massage bed (mostly helpful to somewhat helpful), deep breathing/focus on calm thinking and pain release (somewhat helpful), massage therapy/chiro (both very helpful), acupuncture/IMS/trigger point release (somewhat helpful), prolotherapy (little help), cortisone injection/prednisone/topical cortisone (extremely helpful), epsom salt soaks (somewhat helpful), rolfing therapy (helpful but painful), active release therapy (helpful), pool therapy (somewhat helpful), yoga therapy (helpful) , gentle leg traction to realign sacrum/si joint/hips (helpful), short-duration inversion therapy (helpful), spinal decompression therapy very unhelpful and actually hurt me), qi gong and yoga (somewhat helpful), kinesiology (somewhat helpful), exercise program run by an EDS ignorant physiotherapist (very unhelpful - told me to push through the pain/suck it up which worsened my injuries), distraction by using things I enjoy ie.; crafting, watching educational tutorials when I can't craft, getting outside for a change of scenery, etc. (helpful), foot reflexology (somewhat helpful), positive thinking/focus on positives when pain is bad (somewhat helpful), stretching (very helpful), bracing (helpful), and likely a few more that I've missed.
